{"lemma":"صَمْتُ","slug":"صَمْتُ","root":"ص.م.ت","root_slug":"ص-م-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-م-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24867"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be silent, to be taciturn, to hold one's tongue, to hush up, to be quiet, to become quiet","examples":[{"text":"Hadith\nمَنْ كَانَ يُؤْمِنُ بِٱللّٰهِ وَٱلْيَوْمِ ٱلْآخِرِ فَلْيَقُلْ خَيْرًا أَوْ لِيَصْمُتْ\nman kāna yuʔminu bi-l-lāhi wal-yawmi l-ʔāḵiri falyaqul ḵayran ʔaw liyaṣmut","english":"Whoever believes in God and the Last Day, let him speak good or keep silent."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to silence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَمَتَ (ṣamata) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"silence","examples":[{"text":"فِي صَمْت (fī ṣamt, “silently, quietly”)"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24867","headword_ar":"صَمَتَ","root":"Smt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SamotN","text_ar":"صَمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SumotN","text_ar":"صُمْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SumuwtN","text_ar":"صُمُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SumaAtN","text_ar":"صُمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) or the first of these is the inf. n. and the rest are simple substs.; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASmt","text_ar":"اصمت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSomaAtN","text_ar":"اـِصْمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sm~t","text_ar":"صمّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSomiytN","text_ar":"تَصْمِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K; but only the inf. n. is mentioned;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, silent, mute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speechless;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakata","text_ar":"سَكَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long silent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speechless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh:) but there is a difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakata","text_ar":"سَكَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Samata","text_ar":"صَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for the former is said of him who has the power, or faculty, of speech, but abstains from making use of it; whereas the latter is sometimes said of that which has not the power, or faculty, of speech. (Er-Rághib, MF and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"skt","text_ar":"سكت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) The Arabs say, (Ks, TA,) and it is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Samota yawomFA A_ilaY All~ayoli","text_ar":"لَا صَمْتَ يَوْمًا اـِلَى اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomK","text_ar":"يَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no keeping silence a whole day"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ks, K, TA. [In the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer, ” we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA SumaAta","text_ar":"لا صُمَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA Samota","text_ar":"لا صَمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and El-Munáwee, in his Commentary on that work, says that the keeping silence for a whole day is forbidden by the words of this trad. because it is an imitation of a Christian custom.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*onuhaA SumaAtuhaA","text_ar":"اـِذْنُهَا صُمَاتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in another trad., relating to the asking a virgin if she consent to be married, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Her permission is her silence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her silence is"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her permission,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. it suffices. (Msb.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a bimaA SaA='a waSamata","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ بِمَا صَا=ءَ وَصَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought what was vocal and what was mute"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA SaA='a","text_ar":"مَا صَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, and camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Samata","text_ar":"مَا صَمَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold and silver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaA='a","text_ar":"صَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this saying is formed by transposition from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaA^aY","text_ar":"صَاَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SA^Y","text_ar":"صاى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","L","TA","Ks","IAar"]}]}}